<task id="013" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-A-11 (continued) — Q9 Migration Regression Test Gate (Staging Validation)</title>
    <phase>Phase A — Data-driven Foundation</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>012</dependencies>
    <blocks>028</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, integration-test, ai, chat, migration</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Validation gate task; runs existing regression suite + adds end-to-end smoke against staging; no new `.cs` implementation (test additions only).</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Sequential gate after 012; must complete before Pillar 3 tasks (020+) start.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Run the Q9 batch-migration regression test gate. Validate that all 10 migrated chat
    tools (task 012) are functional in staging through end-to-end exercise: invoke each
    tool from a chat session, verify the response matches pre-migration expected behavior,
    confirm telemetry events emit ADR-015-compliant payloads, confirm safety pipeline
    middleware chain (NFR-13) wraps every invocation, confirm conversational primacy
    (NFR-01) — agent answers conversationally between tool calls.

    Critical-path context: this is the gate task that blocks Pillar 3 (tasks 020-023) and
    the rest of Phase A from continuing. A red gate = roll back task 012 per its documented
    plan; do NOT continue to Pillar 3 until this gate is green.

    Test approach: (a) load the 60+ unit tests authored in task 012 → all green;
    (b) add end-to-end integration tests that exercise each tool through the real chat-agent
    pipeline against a staging Dataverse environment; (c) confirm rollback drill still
    works (one tool removed → fallback to hardcoded → restore).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF QA engineer with integration-test experience. Familiar with the chat-agent
    pipeline + staging deployment + ADR-015 trace verification + NFR-13 safety pipeline.
  </role>

  <goal>
    All 10 migrated chat tools verified functional in staging via end-to-end test.
    60+ unit regression tests green. Rollback drill re-verified. Telemetry payloads
    confirmed ADR-015-compliant. Safety pipeline + conversational primacy verified.
    Gate green; Pillar 3 unblocked.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="migration-evidence">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/notes/task-012-migration-evidence.md</file>
    <file purpose="rollback-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/notes/task-012-rollback-plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="factory">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SprkChatAgentFactory.cs</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Telemetry verification — confirm only tool name + decision + timestamp logged; no user message content.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">No new feature flags introduced in test infrastructure.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish-size delta = 0 (tests only). Report explicitly.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-01">Conversational primacy preserved through end-to-end test.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-13">Safety pipeline middleware chain wraps every tool invocation; confirm via integration test.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-12">Acceptance: incremental per Q9 — but Q9 chose batch; this gate validates the batch landed without regression.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>bff-api/integration-test</topic>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/patterns/testing/unit-test-structure.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/testing/mocking-patterns.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-015-ai-data-governance.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-029-bff-publish-hygiene.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/chat-architecture.md</file>
      <file>docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">
      Output: "🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: STANDARD — integration test + validation gate; tests-only addition".
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Verify 012 ✅. Update `current-task.md` to task 013.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Re-run 60+ Unit Tests">
      Run all task 012 unit regression tests locally. MUST be 100% green.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Add End-to-End Integration Tests">
      For each of 10 migrated tools, add an integration test that exercises the tool through the chat-agent pipeline (real DI graph; staged Dataverse rows; safety middleware applied). Verify: response shape matches pre-migration; telemetry events emit tool name + decision + timestamp only; no user content logged; safety pipeline applied.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Conversational Primacy E2E Test">
      Test asserting: chat agent responds conversationally between tool invocations (NFR-01); refinement / follow-up / context-injection still work.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Re-execute Rollback Drill">
      Delete one `sprk_analysistool` row in staging → confirm task 011's fallback re-activates with hardcoded class; re-insert row → confirm data-driven path returns. Record evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Telemetry Audit">
      Inspect staging logs for last 10 tool invocations; confirm zero entries contain user message text. Record evidence in `notes/task-013-telemetry-audit.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="🛑 Gate Sign-off">
      All checks green = gate PASSED; report and unblock Pillar 3. Any red = gate FAILED; execute task 012 rollback plan; reset to PR-revert state; do NOT continue.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status complete. TASK-INDEX 013 ✅. Reset `current-task.md`. Report gate result + evidence file paths.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">test (unit + integration)</tool>
    <tool name="pac">staging Dataverse row manipulation for rollback drill</tool>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__read_query">MCP — query staging rows for verification</tool>
    <tool name="git">stage + commit test additions</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="test">tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/MigratedToolsIntegrationTests.cs (NEW)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (013 🔲 → ✅)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/current-task.md (reset)</output>
    <output type="notes" ephemeral="true">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/notes/task-013-gate-evidence.md</output>
    <output type="notes" ephemeral="true">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/notes/task-013-telemetry-audit.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All 60+ unit regression tests from task 012 are green.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">10 end-to-end integration tests pass (one per migrated tool).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Conversational primacy E2E test passes (NFR-01).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Safety pipeline middleware chain confirmed wrapping every tool invocation (NFR-13).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Telemetry audit shows zero entries with user message content (ADR-015).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Rollback drill re-executed: tool row delete → hardcoded fallback re-activates → tool row restore → data-driven path returns.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Gate decision recorded (green/red) with evidence; Pillar 3 unblock confirmed.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (tests only).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
